title: High five! - In Photos: What Stimulus Means For Global Stock Markets - Forbes
text:
What Stimulus Means For Global Stock Markets
Investors often complain about the government getting in their way. But they never complain about Central Banks getting in their way. Wait and see what happens when Central Banks actually do get out of the markets way and "taper off" its stimulus. To get a look at the markets sans-stimuli, all you have to do is look beyond the economies of the world whose Central Banks have been driving up equity prices all year. First a look at the benefactors. Then a look at what stock markets have done without monetary stimulus.
